# Component Generalization

Prefer **generalized, reusable components** over ad-hoc props and inline overrides.

## Principles

1. **Minimize custom attributes** — Avoid forcing consumers to repeat layout fixes (e.g. `alignSelf`, `textAlign`) when the component can handle it internally.
2. **Encode common patterns as props** — If a layout or style is used repeatedly, bake it into the component API.
3. **Generalize, don't specialize** — One flexible component (`heading` prop) beats many one-off wrappers.
4. **Favor convention over configuration** — Sensible defaults reduce repetition. Add props only when variation is needed.

## Example

```jsx
// ❌ BAD — consumer must remember layout overrides
<MiraContentSlide centered>
  <Heading alignSelf="flex-start" style={{ textAlign: 'left' }}>Title</Heading>
  ...
</MiraContentSlide>

// ✅ GOOD — component owns the pattern
<MiraContentSlide heading="Title" centered>
  ...
</MiraContentSlide>
```
